<font color="#FF0000">TEACHING ABOUT VIETNAM</font><br>
<tt>Wed Mar 26 10:17:17 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
In 1970, when I was in Cuba I met with representatives <br>
from the N.L.F. They were soldier recognized for<br>
heroism in battle. One of these soldiers said to me<br>
that he held no animosity towards the people of the<br>
United States. It was the governmet and its policies <br>
that he was fighting against. His warmth and openness<br>
during that visit convinced me of this. <br><br>
We need to teach that governments and the people<br>
they claim to represent are ot the same. Soldiers<br>
on the froont lines and the commanders in the rear<br>
do not have the same information and responsibility.<br>
We must not  hold the soldier responsible for the<br>
war, and we must not relieve the Gov't and the <br>
interests they represented of their responsibility
